body:
Can we get a Jira attached to this?
I can open one if you need me to @dataminion 
without it the ASF bots aren't happy
@gustavstickley can you do a pull on the current branch and resolve your merge conflicts?

@gustavstickley additionally can you please open a ticket in the spot Jira this may feel redundant but the T800 merge bot will not merge unless we can resolve a Jira ticket

https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPOT/

Hi @kunalnangia this branch has been open for review for the last weeks. I think we need to check with @EverLoSa and see if the review time has ended. If he says it's over, we need to create a new pull request adding a description for all the changes included in this PR and ask for the finals +1.

Please close this PR and let's wait for @EverLoSa.

Thanks.

Hi @kunalnangia and @rabarona 

The branch hasn't been merged because we are working in a migration script to move the Spot data from CSVs to GraphQL (parquet), once the script is ready we are going start the voting process to merge the branch to the master.

Regards
Ever

this looks pretty good, although it would be nice to have a proxy word creation test
this changeset seems appropriate for adding such a test since it is about proxy word creation
The documentation needs to be updated before we merge this change into the master

Working Fine, performance improvements runtime.
And I see new line comment, SuspiciousConnectsAnalysis: Fitting probabilistic model to data.
does this have any effect on running the script besides getting rid of the warning message?

I'll add some material to address SPOT-163

but what we probably really need somewhere is a "hey to configure your /etc/spot.conf" document

looks good to me

we should we some kind of blog post or collateral explaining the intended use cases and effects of the different options... if used in the wrong scenario (eg. a very small dataset), there won't be any observable affect
unit tests passing and test cluster run passes (I ran it on prod in /home/duxbury/test_ml with ml_ops_oni.sh which sources /etc/spot_oni.conf)

I just noticed the conflicts.

Ricardo - could you resolve the conflicts and resubmit?

hi Gustavo ---

It looks good, although I would prefer throughout that the SparkSession object be called "sparkSession" instead of "spark" ... "spark" almost makes it sound like some kind of fixed object universal to all spark implementations and not a user-configured session object

also, you should merge in the conflicts and resubmit (they are probably no big deal)
Right, I need to rebase my branch with the current master branch.
we'll have to reserve the conflicts before we can merge

minor comments
o/w looks good

contingent LGTM :)

Looks really interesting.

on a side note, I thought we had .gitignore rules for things like this?
[.pyc file](https://github.com/apache/incubator-spot/pull/68/files#diff-d0153f2426f2bda8391e0432aa3efa30)
I think we should remove this file and I will open a PR to change the .gitignore.

We had some issues with partitions being created as Strings but passed to hive as Int's and dropping the leading 0's on days/months < 10.
Curious if this should still be a problem as Hive had some patches regarding this. (I couldn't find them just now but saw it before)

Also do these need to be added to current setup scripts?
I think this could lead to more discussion about pipelines or data sources that someone may choose not to use, should those tables still be generated? 
Perhaps we should move everything into an  *.hql.template and require the .template to be removed for the bash script to pick it up?
Remove reference to Open Network Insight
